723186f-a.title: Manhattan: Sheridan Square - Barrow Street
723186f-a.text:
3-4, 5 Sheridan Square, south side, at and adjoining the corner of Barrow Street. The Greenwich Village Inn is No. 5-6, which is
not all included in the view.
May 1, 1V33.
.. Sperr.  P. I

723187f-a.title: Manhattan: Sheridan Square - Barrow Street
723187f-a.text:
Greenwich Village Inn, 5-6 Sheridan Square, south side, between Barrow and Grove Streets, one of the oldest and best known of Village night clubs, since the closing of Don Dickerman's "Firate's Den'
on Christopher Street.
May 1, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
